This paper deals with the problem of curating labeled training data, which is a common issue in machine learning. The proposed method involves using generative models to synthesize labels at scale from weak supervision sources, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on learning the structure of generative models without labeled data, which is a problem that is relevant to all of these sub-categories.
